The world is mourning the loss of Hollywood actor Burt Reynolds after it was confirmed he died on Thursday morning, aged 82. His agent confirmed he died at the Jupiter Medical Center in Florida. Reynold starred in blockbusters includingBoogie NightsÂ andThe Best Little Whorehouse in Texas. His ability to transcend movie genres and self-mocking attitude made him a firm fan favourite. His love affair with audiences spanned decades and fans have taken to social media to pay tribute to the actor. Well-known Hollywood stars have also paid their respects to Reynolds with Arnold Schwarzenegger calling Reynolds one of his "heroes" and a "trailblazer." Actor Adam Sandler said Reynolds was a "true legend" and "badass."